cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for multimodal subspace clustering, which involves techniques from machine learning, computer vision, and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves self-expressive layer and affinity matrix, which are common in unsupervised learning and clustering, indicating a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
